orm, this volume—supplemented with a series of illustrative drawings and diagrams—will be a necessary addition to the bookshelf of anyone interested in literature, theater, or classical studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aeuripides, sophocles, aeschylus, ancient greece, drama, performing arts, music, dance, theater, tragedy, chorus, space, stage, performance, orchestra, classicism, chant, song, altar, tombs, eumenides, libation bearers, agamemnon, oresteia, seven against thebes, suppliants, persians, choros, vocal delivery, movement, epic, melody, measure, meter, nonfiction, literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022647757240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226477565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226477565/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles